      {
        "paragraph_index": 2,
        "text": "Interpretation\n- 94 distinct ligands in SRD‑46 have been studied with both iron(II) and iron(III) (derived by counting ligands that have ligand–metal “card” records with both metal_61 and metal_62).\n- On the question “is the complex consistently more stable with Fe³⁺ for those ligands?”, a definitive, apples‑to‑apples comparison requires matching stoichiometry (e.g., ML vs ML), medium/supporting electrolyte, temperature, and ionic strength before comparing logβ(Fe³⁺) to logβ(Fe²⁺). That computation was not completed in this run, so I cannot assert consistency across all 94 ligands here.",
