        "paragraph_index": 3,
        "text": "Chemistry note\n- Generally, Fe³⁺ (higher charge, higher charge density) tends to show larger overall formation constants than Fe²⁺ for a given ligand, especially for hard O‑donor ligands. However, hydrolysis of Fe³⁺ and variations in medium/ionic strength can alter conditional stability, so a matched‑conditions analysis is needed to confirm the trend ligand‑by‑ligand.",
